Current Situation
We are in the process of migrating our build system from Ant to Gradle.
The current system is a monolithic Ant build, where multiple targets are tightly coupled. This makes builds slow, difficult to maintain, and hard to evolve.
What has already been done:
We merged a Gradle wrapper into the Ant build
Several targets have already been partially converted to Gradle
Initial dependency and structural issues have been identified
2. Why Gradle Wrapper Was Needed
The Gradle wrapper was introduced to support a gradual migration strategy.
Instead of switching everything at once:
Gradle builds can now be executed from within the Ant build
Existing workflows remain functional
We can migrate targets step by step without breaking the system
This allows us to safely transition while continuing development.
3. Migration Approach (Phase 1)
We are following an incremental migration strategy:
Convert each target individually from Ant to Gradle
Merge each converted target into the main branch
Continue until all targets are migrated
Once completed, the Gradle wrapper inside Ant will be removed
Execution plan:
Maximum of 1 converted target merged every 2–3 days
Multiple targets can be converted in parallel
After each merge, other targets must be revalidated, because they depend on each other
4. Conversion Flow
For each target:
Convert Ant build logic to Gradle
Ensure required files are downloaded, unpacked, and prepared
Validate integration with other targets
Merge into main branch
Example observation:
After converting one target, it successfully downloads and prepares files for other targets
The next target exposed additional complexity and required deeper investigation
5. Blockers Identified
During conversion of subsequent targets, we identified a major blocker:
Shared copyright injection logic:
Implemented as a common build class
Used across many projects
Not all code follows required copyright standards
This required deeper analysis and team discussion.
6. Solution Implemented
We decided to:
Move the shared logic into a separate repository
Consolidate all related files and constants into one common class
Standardize usage across all builds
This removes duplication and ensures consistency.
7. Current Progress
Gradle wrapper integrated into Ant ✅
Multiple targets already converted (initial work completed) ✅
Common copyright solution implemented ✅
Previously, teams were blocked waiting for this shared component.
Now:
